isplay=inline}} -->\n| burial_place       =  <!-- may be used instead of resting_place and resting_place_coordinates - displays \"Burial place\" as label -->\n| burial_coordinates =  <!-- {{coord|LAT|LONG|type:landmark|display=inline}} -->\n| monuments          = \n| residence          = \n| nationality        = \n| other_names        = \n| citizenship        = \n| education          = [[MBA]] in finance and economics\n| alma_mater         = [[New York University]], [[Stern School of Business]]\n| occupation         = Founder and CEO of Bija Advisors LLC, Lecturer at [[University of California]], Artist, Author\n| years_active       = \n| era                = \n| employer           = \n| organization       = \n| agent              =  <!-- Discouraged in most cases, specifically when promotional, and requiring a reliable source -->\n| known_for          = Incorporating [[Cognitive Science]] with [[Investment Management]],<ref>{{cite news|last1=Greenberg|first1=Greg|title=Powerless Fed Can't Stop Stocks From Heading Higher, Says Bija CIO|url=http://www.thestreet.com/story/13188471/1/what-does-cognitive-science-have-to-do-with-investing-lots-says-stephen-duneier.html|accessdate=December 9, 2015|publisher=The Street|date=June 16, 2015}}</ref> [[Yarnbombing]] in the Wilderness,<ref>{{cite news|last1=Dinaberg|first1=Leslie|title=The Art of Getting People Back to Nature|url=http://sbseasons.com/2015/06/yarnbomber-stephen-duneier/|accessdate=December 9, 2015|publisher=SB Seasons|date=June 16, 2015}}</ref> Extreme Goal Achievement\n| notable_works      =  <!-- produces label \"Notable work\"; may be overridden by |credits=, which produces label \"Notable credit(s)\"; or by |works=, which produces label \"Works\" -->\n| style              = \n| home_town          = \n| salary             = \n| net_worth          =  <!-- Net worth should be supported with a citation from a reliable source -->\n| height             =  <!-- \"X cm\", \"X m\"  or \"X ft Y in\" plus optional reference (conversions are automatic) -->\n| weight             =  <!-- \"X kg\", \"X lb\" or \"X st Y lb\" plus optional reference (conversions are automatic) -->\n| television         = \n| title              = \n| term               = \n| predecessor        = \n| successor          = \n| party              = \n| movement           = \n| opponents          = \n| boards             = \n| religion           =  <!-- Religion should be supported with a citation from a reliable source -->\n| denomination       =  <!-- Denomination should be supported with a citation from a reliable source -->\n| criminal_charge    =  <!-- Criminality parameters should be supported with citations from reliable sources -->\n| criminal_penalty   = \n| criminal_status    = \n| spouse             =  Barbara\n| partner            =  <!-- (unmarried long-term partner) -->\n| children           = \n| parents            = \n| relatives          = \n| callsign           = \n| awards             = \n| website            =  {{URL|BijaAdvisorsLLC.com}}, {{URL|Yarnbomber.com}}, {{URL|TheLPE.com}}\n| module             = \n| module2            = \n| module3            = \n| module4            = \n| module5            = \n| module6            = \n| signature          = \n| signature_size     = \n| signature_alt      = \n| footnotes          = \n| ethnicity          =  <!-- Ethnicity should be supported with a citation from a reliable source -->\n}}\n'''Stephen Duneier''' is an American professional investment manager, strategy consultant, speaker, lecturer, author, artist and Guinness World Record holder.\n\n==Education==\nDuneier attended the [[University of Florida]] from 1985 to 1987 before leaving to pursue a career in financial management with [[Drexel Burnham Lambert]] and then [[Prudential-Bache]]. He finished his undergraduate education at [[Florida Atlantic University]] with a BBA in finance and economics and received an [[MBA]] in finance and economics from [[New York University]]'s [[Stern School of Business]].<ref>{{cite web|title=CEO, Stephen Duneier|url=http://www.bijaadvisorsllc.com/ceo-stephen-duneier.html|website=Bija Advisors LLC|publisher=Bija Advisors LLC|accessdate=December 9, 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Career in Finance==\nWhile still attending graduate school at [[NYU]], Duneier worked as a foreign exchange option trader specializing in exotic derivatives at [[Credit Suisse]] in New York City. He was later hired by [[Bank of America]] to expand their foreign exchange business into European crosses and [[Emerging Markets]] and eventually promoted to Global Head of Currency Option Trading. Soon after Bank of America merged with Nations Bank, Duneier moved to AIG International where he was eventually named managing director in charge of Emerging Markets trading and based out of London, England. In 2002, Duneier launched a proprietary trading portfolio known as \"TIP\" for AIG International.<ref>{{cite web|title=Creation of Additional Incubator Fund|url=http://www.investegate.co.uk/sgam-a-i--starway-fd/rns/creation-of-additional-incuba/200809021630065818C/|website=FE Investegate|accessdate=December 9, 2015}}</ref> Shortly after the firm merged with Banque AIG, Duneier became a global macro portfolio manager at London Diversified Fund Management in London and later at Peloton Partners in [[Santa Barbara, California]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Drobny|first1=Andres|title=Drobny Global Monitor|url=http://www.drobny.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/Conference-Review-Santa-Monica-2009-19.pdf|website=Drobny|publisher=Drobny Global|accessdate=December 9, 2015}}</ref> In 2008, he was one of the founding partners at Grant Capital Partners<ref>{{cite web|title=Alternative Investment News|url=http://www.strandfund.com/images/Alternative_Investment_News_October_2008.pdf|website=Strand Fund|publisher=Total Alternatives|accessdate=December 9, 2015}}</ref> which grew to $1.25&nbsp;billion in assets under management.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Friedman|first1=Steven|title=Stephen Duneier; Bija Advisors|url=https://www.santangelsreview.com/stephen-duneier-bija-advisors/|website=Santangels Review|accessdate=December 9, 2015}}</ref> He left in 2012 to launch Bija Capital Management and eventually Bija Advisors LLC, a consulting firm which advises experienced hedge fund managers, CIO's and asset allocators. Through Bija Advisors, he speaks on and publishes a subscription based newsletter covering topics on economics,<ref>{{cite news|last1=Xie|first1=Ye|title=Dollar Turning Point Aided by U.S. Investor Reversal: Currencies|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2014-10-20/dollar-turning-point-aided-by-u-s-investor-reversal-currencies|accessdate=December 9, 2015|publisher=Bloomberg|date=October 19, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Lloyd|first1=Colin|title=Will Europe Benefit Economically from the Migrant Crisis|url=http://www.nasdaq.com/article/will-europe-benefit-economically-from-the-migrant-crisis-cm524368|accessdate=December 9, 2015|agency=Seeking Alpha|publisher=Nasdaq|date=September 25, 2015}}</ref> cognitive science,<ref>{{cite web|title=Cognitive science exposes a serious mistake made by most asset allocators|url=http://2n20.com/opinion-cognitive-science-exposes-a-serious-mistake-made-by-most-asset-allocators/|website=2n20.com|publisher=2n20 AG|accessdate=December 9, 2015}}</ref> and investment management.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Chen|first1=Vivian|title=AUM's Impact on Performance|url=http://www.pmjar.com/?p=1589|website=PM Jar|accessdate=December 9, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Duneier|first1=Stephen|title=Declawing the Federal Reserve|url=http://advisorhubinc.com/declawing-of-the-federal-reserve-2/|accessdate=December 9, 2015|publisher=Advisor Hub|date=July 9, 2015}}</ref> Duneier's book, ''AlphaBrain'' is due for release in early 2019 (Wiley & Sons).\n\n==Career as a cognitive science practitioner==\nIn 2001, Duneier began to apply his approach to decision making, which he calls \"Bija\", to his personal life, leading to a long string of eccentric goals and resolutions being set and achieved.<ref>{{cite web|title=The Secret to Successful New Year's Resolutions|url=http://www.bijaadvisorsllc.com/the-secret-to-successful-new-years-resolutions.html|website=Bija Advisors LLC|publisher=Bija Advisors LLC|accessdate=December 9, 2015}}</ref> In 2012, it reached fever pitch when he embarked upon 12 for 2012,<ref>{{cite web|title=12 for 2012|url=http://12for2012.com/|website=12for2012|accessdate=December 9, 2015}}</ref> a New Year's resolution which included 12 Learning Resolutions and 12 Giving Resolutions.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Burgess|first1=Phil|title=Bonus Years: New year is good time to commit to new learning and giving|url=http://www.capitalgazette.com/lifestyle/health/ph-ac-cl-bonus-1227-20151227-story.html|accessdate=December 28, 2015|publisher=Capital Gazette|date=December 27, 2015}}</ref> As part of his resolutions, he has performed at [[comedy clubs]], learned to fly a [[helicopter]], climbed iced waterfalls, raced cars, had [[root canal]] without anesthetic, learned to speak German, read 50 books in 52 weeks,<ref>{{cite web|last1=Mills|first1=Ted|title=Episode 24: The Yarnbomber|url=http://www.funkzonepodcast.com/?p=251|website=Funkzone Podcast|accessdate=December 9, 2015}}</ref> participated in the Pier to Peak [[half marathon]], learned to [[unicycle]], used [[jumping stilts]] to hike, fostered a [[pit bull]], built homes for families in [[Arizona]], learned [[ballroom dancing]], how to drum, [[slackline]], [[parkour]], [[skydive]] and flown planes acrobatically.{{citation needed|date=January 2016}}\n\nHe set the Guinness World Record for the largest crocheted [[granny square]]. It is 1,311 square feet, incorporates more than 30 miles of yarn and weighs over 60 pounds. It took  2 years, 7 months and 17 days to create, and required more than 500,000 double crochet stitches.<ref>{{cite web|title=Yarnbomber Achieves World Record for Largest Granny Square|url=http://blog.redheart.com/world-record-granny-square-achieved/|website=Heart Strings by Red Heart Yarns|publisher=Red Heart|accessdate=8 August 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Vercillo|first1=Kathryn|title=5 Shockingly Humongous Crochet Blankets|url=http://crochet.about.com/od/crochetcommunity/tp/5-Shockingly-Humongous-Crochet-Blankets.htm|website=About.com|accessdate=December 9, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=World Record Attempt|url=http://www.yarnbomber.com/world-record-attempt.html|website=Yarnbomber.com|accessdate=December 9, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.guinnessworldrecords.com/Account/Login?ReturnUrl=%2fsearch%2fapplicationrecordsearch%3fterm%3d%2522largest%2bcrochet%2bsquare%2522%26contentType%3drecord&term=%22largest+crochet+square%22&contentType=record|title=Sign in|website=Guinness World Records|access-date=2016-12-12}}</ref>\n\nDuneier now speaks<ref>{{cite web|title=Speaker Inspires Monroe Students|url=https://www.sbunified.org/2015/03/13/speaker-inspires-monroe-students/|website=Santa Barbara Unified|publisher=Santa Barbara Unified School District|accessdate=December 9, 2015}}</ref> and writes about his experience and how others can take what we have learned from research conducted in the field of [[cognitive science]] in order to make better decisions and achieve bigger goals.<ref>{{cite web|title=Volunteer Spotlight: Stephen Duneier|url=http://youthinteractive.tumblr.com/post/113980039096/volunteer-spotlight-stephen-duneier|website=Youth Interactive|publisher=Youth Interactive|accessdate=December 9, 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Career as a Lecturer==\nDuneier teaches undergraduate and graduate level courses on [[Decision Analysis]] in the College of Engineering at the [[University of California in Santa Barbara]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Lecturers|url=http://www.tmp.ucsb.edu/about/lecturers/stephen-duneier|website=Technology Management Program, UCSB|publisher=University of California|accessdate=December 9, 2015}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Cold Spring Yarnbomb Installation by Stephen Duneier.JPG|thumb|40 ft tall eucalyptus tree 2.6 miles up the Cold Spring Trail wrapped with yarn.]]\n\n==Career as an Artist==\nDuneier is an [[installation artist]], part of the fiber-art movement known as [[Yarnbombing]].<ref>{{cite news|last1=Rogan|first1=Jack|title=The Yarnbomber|url=https://rootsrated.com/stories/yarnbomber|accessdate=December 9, 2015|publisher=Roots Rated|date=April 9, 2014}}</ref> His installations exist for just 9 days typically in [[Los Padres National Forest]].<ref>{{cite web|title=About Yarnbomber|url=http://www.yarnbomber.com/about.html|website=Yarnbomber.com|accessdate=December 9, 2015}}</ref>\n\nAs part of his 2012 resolution to learn 12 new skills, Duneier learned how to knit. His first project was the covering of a 40-foot tall eucalyptus tree, 2.6 miles up the Cold Spring Trail in [[Santa Barbara, California]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Hemmons|first1=Jessie|title=Interview with Yarnbomber Stephen Duneier|url=http://www.ishknits.com/interview-with-yarnbomber-stephen-duneier/|website=IshKnits.com|accessdate=December 9, 2015}}</ref> It required 450 square feet of knitted material. The installation remained for just 9 days and all material used was donated to Warm Up America, a charity in [[North Carolina]].\n\nThe following year he wrapped a massive boulder atop the Saddlerock hiking trail above [[Montecito, California]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Hiking Saddlerock|url=http://www.santabarbaracompany.com/blogs/blog/11914285-hiking-saddlerock|website=The Santa Barbara Company|publisher=The Santa Barbara Company|accessdate=December 9, 2015}}</ref> [[File:Saddlerock Yarnbomb by Stephen Duneier.jpg|thumb|Photo of the 2013 yarnbomb installation by Stephen Duneier atop Saddlerock in the mountains above Montecito California.]]\n\nHis third installation was a large spiderweb made out of yarn which covered Sasquatch Cave in The Playgrounds at Lizard's Mouth. [[File:Spiderweb Yarnbomb Installation by Stephen Duneier.JPG|thumb|Sasquatch Cave at Lizards Mouth in Santa Barbara California]]\n\nFor his fourth installation, Duneier created a giant starfish made with reflective yarn from Red Heart Yarns and hung it 40 feet above the Seven Falls Trail. [[File:Starfish Yarnbomb Installation by Stephen Duneier.jpg|thumb|Seven Falls Trail in the mountains of Santa Barbara California]]\n\nHis fifth installation occurred at [[Santa Barbara City College]] where he laid out nearly 2,500 square feet of knitted and crocheted pieces on their lawn. [[File:SBCC Yarnbomb by Stephen Duneier.PNG|thumb|2,500 square feet of knitted and crocheted material laid out at SBCC in Santa Barbara.]]\n\n[[File:Lizards Mouth Yarnbomb by Stephen Duneier.jpg|thumb|18 massive boulders wrapped with yarn at Lizard's Mouth in Los Padres National Forest above Santa Barbara, CA.]]\n\nFor his sixth installation, he invited fiber artists from around the world to collaborate with him by sending crocheted and knitted pieces of any size, shape, color and style to participate. He received contributions from 388 artists in 36 countries and all 50 US States. Combined with his own work, he wrapped 18 giant boulders at Lizards Mouth<ref>{{cite news|last1=Lehr|first1=Tracy|title=Knitter Creates Unusual Art|url=http://www.keyt.com/news/knitter-creates-unusual-art/26378886|accessdate=December 9, 2015|publisher=KEYT KCOY|date=June 6, 2014}}</ref> in the [[Los Padres National Forest]] above [[Santa Barbara, California|Santa Barbara]] in California.\n[[File:Alien Campsite yarnbomb installation by Stephen Duneier.jpg|thumb|10 aliens and 24 tents covered with yarn line the canyon at Davey Brown Trailhead above Santa Ynez in California.]]\nHis most recent project was called the Alien Campsite<ref>{{cite web|last1=Stewart|first1=Ethan|title=The Santa Barbara YarnBomber Strikes Again, But Gets Foiled by Mother Nature|url=https://rootsrated.com/stories/the-santa-barbara-yarnbomber-strikes-gets-foiled-mother-nature|website=Roots Rated|publisher=Roots Rated|accessdate=December 9, 2015}}</ref> where he incorporated additional materials including [[fiberglass]], wood, and metal in addition to [[yarn]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Alien Campsite|url=http://blog.redheart.com/alien-campsite/|website=Heart Strings|publisher=Red Heart Yarns|accessdate=December 9, 2015}}</ref> He created 10 aliens and 24 tents for the installation which lasted just 36 hours before being ripped apart by high winds in the canyon. The installation was permitted by the [[US Forest Service]] for the area just below the Davey Brown Trailhead. It incorporated Duneier's own work plus contributions from 656 fiber artists from 41 countries and all 50 states.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Cooper|first1=Arnie|title=The Guerrilla Art of the Yarn Bomb Goes Natural|url=http://www.newsweek.com/guerilla-art-yarn-bomb-goes-natural-312069|accessdate=December 9, 2015|publisher=Newsweek Magazine|date=March 8, 2015}}</ref> \nDuneier's work is represented by the Sullivan Goss Gallery.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Stewart|first1=Ethan|title=Knitting Psychedelic Daydreams|url=http://www.independent.com/news/2014/sep/11/knitting-psychedelic-day-dreams/|accessdate=December 9, 2015|publisher=The Santa Barbara Independent|date=September 11, 2014}}</ref>\n\nAs part of his stated mission to build a global community kind and creative people,<ref>{{cite web|last1=Martin|first1=Jordana|title=Ultimate Yarn Bomber: Steve Duneier|url=http://textileartscenter.com/blog/ultimate-yarn-bomber-steve-duneier/|website=Textile Arts Center|publisher=Textile Arts Center|accessdate=December 9, 2015}}</ref> Duneier hosts the Yarnbomber podcast in which he features interviews with famous yarnbombers from around the world including Carol Hummel, London Kaye and Jessie Hemmons.<ref>{{cite web|title=Yarnbomber Podcast|url=https://itunes.apple.com/tc/podcast/yarnbomber-podcast/id1016663275|website=iTunes|publisher=Apple|accessdate=December 9, 2015}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[Cognitive bias]]\n*[[Land art]]\n*[[Site-Specific Art]]\n*[[Environmental art]]\n*[[Decision Analysis]]\n*[[B\u012bja|Bija]]\n*[[Yarnbombing]]\n*[[Fiber art]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://BijaAdvisorsLLC.com Official Website of Bija Advisors LLC]\n* [http://yarnbomber.com Official Website of Yarnbomber Stephen Duneier]\n* [http://12for2012.com 2012 New Year's Resolution Blog]\n* [http://TheLPE.com Official Website of The League of Professional Educators]\n* [http://www.tmp.ucsb.edu/about/lecturers/stephen-duneier University of California Santa Barbara TMP Website]\n\n{{Instecon}}\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Duneier, Stephen}}\n[[Category:University of Florida alumni]]\n[[Category:New York University Stern School of Business alumni]]\n[[Category:Florida Atlantic University alumni]]\n[[Category:American financiers]]\n[[Category:American hedge fund managers]]\n[[Category:American investors]]\n[[Category:American management consultants]]\n[[Category:American money managers]]\n[[Category:American chief executives]]\n[[Category:American installation artists]]\n[[Category:21st-century American economists]]\n[[Category:Behavioral economists]]\n[[Category:Behavioral finance]]\n[[Category:American textile artists]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1967 births]]\n", "name_user": "Pelirodri1248", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eCareer as a cognitive science practitioner", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stephen_Duneier"}
{"title_page": "Julma-Henri", "text_new": "{{short description|Finnish rapper}}\n{{BLP sources|date=July 2013}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n|name = Julma-Henri\n|image =  \n|caption = \n|image_size = \n|background = solo_singer\n|alias = {{plainlist |\n*Money <small>(during Forever)</small>\n*Julma-Henri\n*Henri\n*Henkka\n*LL Julma H\n*J\u00e4\u00e4karhu-Make\n*Money\n*Pepsi P\n*JLMA HNRI }}\n|birth_date = \n|origin = [[Oulu]], [[Finland]]\n|instrument = \n|genre = {{plainlist |\n*[[Rap music|Rap]]\n*[[Hardcore hip hop]]\n*[[Horrorcore]]\n*[[Trap music (hip hop)|Trap]]\n*[[Progressive rock]]\n*[[Dubstep]]\n*[[grime (music)|Grime]] }}\n|occupation = [[Rapper]], [[music producer]]\n|years_active = 1998\u2013present \n|label = {{plainlist |\n*\u00c4hky Records (2007\u20132009)\n*M\u00f6rssi (2010\u2013present)\n*Fullsteam Records (2013\u2013present) }}\n|associated_acts = {{plainlist |\n*'''Formations:'''\n*Forever (1998\u20132001)\n*Julma-Henri & Syrj\u00e4ytyneet (2007\u20132010)\n*Julma-Henri & [[RPK (rapper)|RPK]] (2010\u20132012)\n*[[Eurocrack]] (2012\u2013present)\n*'''Various acts:'''\n*[[Steen1]]\n*Panama Rayo\n*Asa\n*[[RPK (rapper)|RPK]]\n*Laineen Kasper\n*Jontti\n*[[Juju (Finnish rapper)|Juju]] }}\n|website = \n}}\n'''Julma-Henri'''  (in  English ''Cruel Henri'') is a Finnish rapper based in Helsinki. In addition to his solo act, he was part of rap band Forever from 1998 to 2001 under the name '''Money'''. He appeared in collective '''Julma-Henri & Syrj\u00e4ytyneet''' (2007\u20132010) and from 2010 strongly collaborated as duo Julma-Henri & RPK.<ref>[http://www.fullsteamrecords.com/app/artist/single/-/id/876 Fullsteam Records: JULMA HENRI & RPK page] {{in lang|fi}}</ref> With [[RPK (rapper)|RPK]], he launched an official duo rap act known as '''[[Eurocrack]]'''<ref name=rumba>{{cite news|url=http://www.rumba.fi/perjantaina-omalaatuiset-levynjulkkarit-keskella-katua-julma-henri-ja-rpk-tarjoavat-euro-crackia-36454/|author= |title=Perjantaina omalaatuiset levynjulkkarit keskell\u00e4 katua \u2013 Julma-Henri ja RPK tarjoavat Euro Crackia|publisher=Rumba.fi|date=28 June 2013|language=Finnish}}</ref>  (stylized as E U R O C R A C K) in 2012.\n\nJulma-Henri is known for his lurid and gritty sociopolitical lyrics. With names such as [[Steen1]] and Panama Rayo, he became famous for having remarkably darker, harder and more serious punk influenced lyrical tone compared to other Finnish rappers, who were famous for their relatively light-minded, punchline-centric lyrics. In the early 2000s, his music and public image were widely associated with [[anarchism]] and proletarian activism and he made a name for himself by performing in illegal parties, political protests and even riots.\n\n==Career==\nJulma-Henri began his career at Forever, a rap band he formed in Oulu in 1998 under the pseudonym Money. The band released the single \"Mobmusic\", a demo EP in 2000. The other members were OeO, Reksa ja Leijona. As Money, he released ''Soundtrack 2 My Life'', a self-financed and independently released album produced by RK-62 and Panama Rayo. In 2003, cooperated with Asa and [[Steen1]]. A number of collaborations followed and he appeared in mixtapes and compilations with notable tracks like \"Mit\u00e4 s\u00e4 tied\u00e4t\" and \"Vaan sil on v\u00e4li\u00e4\". In 2004, he worked on ''Soundtrack 2 My Life'' as a full album with appearances by Steen1, Tasis, Travis Bicle and Afu Ra (USA) \u2013 however, the album was never released.\n\nJulma-Henri found recognition with his debut studio album ''Al-Qaida Finland'' in 2005 while still residing in Oulu. In many of his releases, he used the name '''Julma-Henri & Syrj\u00e4ytyneet''' (Julma-Henri and the Marginalized). Julma-Henri always appears disguised without revealing much of his face. In 2005 and 2006, he had a joint radio show Bassoradio (a collective project of tens of DJs) with Steen 1 as ''Julma-Henri & Yst\u00e4v\u00e4t'' (meaning Julma-Henri & Friends) The title was \"Free Your Mind\" also touring Finland with Asa and Steen 1 and appearing in tracks in releases by them. In 2007, he appeared in a music video with Asa called \"240306\" (aka \"RikRek\"). In May 2007, Panama Rayon and Laineen Kasper reproduced and rereleased Julma-Henri's ''Al-Qaida Finland'' on Colin Records in Helsinki with great success. In January 2008, an all-Finland \"Support Al-Qaida Finland Tour\" was organized assisted by a number of rap and hip hop acts.\n\nBased on this success, he released in December 2008 the mixtape ''SRJTNT Vol 1'' criticizing commercialization of rap. It was produced by Panama Rayo. A number of appearances followed in a series of compilations like Asa's ''Via Karelia'', Aisti & Emeto's ''Exitus'' in the title track and Leijona's album ''Vauhtia ja vaarallisia tilanteita''. His 2009 release ''Outo nauha'' was a split album with Laineen Kasperi. In 2010, he released the album ''Psykoterapia'' again crediting Julma-Henri & Syrj\u00e4ytyneet and dealing, as many of his earlier albums with social exclusion and mental health problems and the dark side of life. The album was released on M\u00f6rssi record label and distributed by Playground Music. A single titled \"Kipu\" (meaning Pain) was released as a single. After ''Psykoterapia'', Julma-Henri & Syrj\u00e4ytyneet assembly broke in 2010 due to disagreements and Julma-Henri proceeded on collaborations with rapper [[RPK (rapper)|RPK]] (of Ceebrolistics fame) with joint ''Kutsu EP'' of 6 tracks released in December 2010 credited to '''Julma-Henri & RPK'''. \"Kutsu\" taken from the album was released as a music video. The follow-up album ''\"HENRI\"'' with 17 tracks from Julma-Henri & RPK in February 2013 produced another music video \"Pala\". Julma-Henri also contributed tracks to albums by Juju and Jontti.\n\nIn December 2011, Julma-Henri released his new album ''Radio Jihad... SRJTNT vol. 2''<ref name=nrgm>[http://www.nrgm.fi/kritiikit/julma-henri-radio-jihad-syrjaytynyt-vol-2/ nrgm.fi Review of Julma-Henri album \u2013 ''Radio Jihad: Syrj\u00e4ytynyt vol. 2''] {{in lang|fi}}</ref> as a follow-up to his successful ''SRJTNT Vol 1''  touching subjects of personal growth, recovery and hope from society's ills. The album was produced by DJ Polarsoul and a number of artists contributed including Asa, Jontti, Juju, Konna, RPK, Super Janne, C-star, Akli ja Joska. Three music videos were released: \"Punainen\", \"Radio Jihad\" and \"Kauppaan kauppaan\"\n\n===Eurocrack===\n{{Main|Eurocrack}}\nAs early as July 2011, and prior to ''Radio Jihad...'' release by Julma-Henri, RPK announced on [[Bassoradio]] that he was collaborating with Julma-Henri on a brand new project called Eurocrack and that an album was in the offing. In preparation, the two released ''Euro Crack EP'' in the July 2012.<ref>{{cite web|last=Tamminen|first=Jari|title=Julma Henri, hyvien puolella|url=http://fifi.voima.fi/artikkeli/2012/heinakuu/julma-henri-hyvien-puolella|publisher=Fifi.voima.fi|accessdate=29 April 2014}}</ref> The EP contained 7 tracks including the epominous ''E.U.R.O.C.R.A.C.K.'' and the track \"Euro Crack Rocks\", the latter with Kube, Aztra, Khid, Klommo, Ameeba & Mindman. A promotional website www.eurocrack.com was launched in preparation. \"Pommi\" from the EP was released as a music video. The two organized a \"Euro Crack Tour\" to promote the project through M\u00f6rss website. The act also announced signing to the [[Fullsteam Records]] in cooperation with M\u00f6rssi.\n\nIn 2013, the track \"Douppii douppaa\" was released as pre-release in music video form in promotion of the debut studio album of Eurocrack (stylized as E U R O C R A C K). The album titled ''Huume'' (stylized as H U U M E) was released on 28 June 2013 entering the Finnish Albums Chart at number 7 in its first week of release.\n\n==Discography==\n\n===Albums, EPs, Mixtapes===\n'''as part of Forever'''\n*2000: ''Mobmusic'' (demo release)\n\n'''as Money'''\n*2003: ''Soundtrack 2 My Life'' <small>(self-released)</small>\n*2004: ''Mob. Ent: Live Mixtape'' <small>(self-released)</small>\n*2004: TBA <small>(full mixtape album, not released)</small>\n\n'''Julma-Henri & Syrj\u00e4ytyneet'''\n*2007: ''Al-Qaida Finland'' <small>(\u00c4hky Records)</small>\n*2008: ''SRJTNT vol. 1'' <small>(mixtape, self-released)</small>\n*2010: ''Psykoterapia'' <small>(M\u00f6rssi)</small>\n\n'''Henri & Kasperi'''\n*2009: ''Outo nauha'' <small>(aplit album with Laineen Kasperi. \u00c4hky Records)</small>\n\n'''Solo'''\n*2011: ''Radio Jihad... SRJTNT vol. 2'' <small>(M\u00f6rssi)</small>\n\n'''as Julma-Henri & RPK'''\n*2010: ''Kutsu EP'' <small>(M\u00f6rssi)</small>\n*2011: ''\"HENRI\"'' <small>(M\u00f6rssi)</small>\n\n'''as Julma-Henri vs RPK'''\n*2012: ''Euro Crack EP'' <small>(M\u00f6rssi)</small>\n\n'''as [[Eurocrack]]'''\n*2013: ''H U U M E'' <small>(M\u00f6rssi / [[Fullsteam Records]])</small>\n\n'''as JULMA H'''\n*2015: JULMA H (M\u00f6rssi / Fullsteam Records)\n*2016: Julma H: Kuka muu muka 2 (M\u00f6rssi Records)\n*2016: Julma H: Musta Albumi (Playground / M\u00f6rssi Records)\n\n===Singles / Music videos===\n*2007: \"240306\" aka \"RikRek\" <small>(Julma-Henri & Syrj\u00e4ytyneet featuring Asa)</small>\n*2009: \"Meitsi on matafaka\" <small>(Julma-Henri & Syrj\u00e4ytyneet)</small>\n*2010: \"Kipu\" <small>(Julma-Henri & Syrj\u00e4ytyneet)</small>\n*2010: \"Kutsu\" <small>(Julma-Henri & RPK)</small>\n*2011: \"Pala\"  <small>(Julma-Henri & RPK)</small>\n*2011: \"Punainen\" <small>(Julma-Henri featuring RPK)</small>\n*2011: \"Radio Jihad\" <small>(Julma-Henri)</small>\n*2012: \"Kauppaan kauppaan\" <small>(Julma-Henri)</small>\n*2012: \"E.U.R.O.C.R.A.C.K.\"  <small>(JLMA HNRI x RPK)</small>\n*2012: \"Savuaa\" <small>(Juju featuring Julma-Henri)</small>\n\n'''Euro Crack / Eurocrack single / music video releases'''\n*2012: \"Pommi\" <small>(JLMA HNRI X RPK / EURO CRACK)</small>\n*2013: \"Spaced Out\" <small>(Eurocrack)</small>\n*2013: \"Douppii douppaa\" <small>(Eurocrack)</small>\n*2013: \"Kr\u00e4kk\u00e4kr\u00e4nkk\u00e4\" <small>(Eurocrack)</small>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://www.facebook.com/JulmaHenri Facebook]\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Julma-Henri}}\n[[Category:Finnish rappers]]\n[[Category:Masked musicians]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Oulu]]\n[[Category:Horrorcore artists]]\n[[Category:Grime music artists]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Finnish rapper}}\n{{BLP sources|date=July 2013}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n|name = Julma-Henri\n|image =  \n|caption = \n|image_size = \n|background = solo_singer\n|alias = {{plainlist |\n*Money <small>(during Forever)</small>\n*Julma-Henri\n*Henri\n*Henkka\n*LL Julma H\n*J\u00e4\u00e4karhu-Make\n*Money\n*Pepsi P\n*JLMA HNRI }}\n|birth_date = \n|origin = [[Oulu]], [[Finland]]\n|instrument = \n|genre = {{plainlist |\n*[[Rap music|Rap]]\n*[[Hardcore hip hop]]\n*[[Horrorcore]]\n*[[Trap music (hip hop)|Trap]]\n*[[Progressive rock]]\n*[[Dubstep]]\n*[[grime (music)|Grime]] }}\n|occupation = [[Rapper]], [[music producer]]\n|years_active = 1998\u2013present \n|label = {{plainlist |\n*\u00c4hky Records (2007\u20132009)\n*M\u00f6rssi (2010\u2013present)\n*Fullsteam Records (2013\u2013present) }}\n|associated_acts = {{plainlist |\n*'''Formations:'''\n*Forever (1998\u20132001)\n*Julma-Henri & Syrj\u00e4ytyneet (2007\u20132010)\n*Julma-Henri & [[RPK (rapper)|RPK]] (2010\u20132012)\n*[[Eurocrack]] (2012\u2013present)\n*'''Various acts:'''\n*[[Steen1]]\n*Panama Rayo\n*Asa\n*[[RPK (rapper)|RPK]]\n*Laineen Kasper\n*Jontti\n*[[Juju (Finnish rapper)|Juju]] }}\n|website = \n}}\n'''Julma-Henri'''  (in  English ''Cruel Henri'') is a Finnish rapper based in Helsinki. In addition to his solo act, he was part of rap band Forever from 1998 to 2001 under the name '''Money'''. He appeared in collective '''Julma-Henri & Syrj\u00e4ytyneet''' (2007\u20132010) and from 2010 strongly collaborated as duo Julma-Henri & RPK.<ref>[http://www.fullsteamrecords.com/app/artist/single/-/id/876 Fullsteam Records: JULMA HENRI & RPK page] {{in lang|fi}}</ref> With [[RPK (rapper)|RPK]], he launched an official duo rap act known as '''[[Eurocrack]]'''<ref name=rumba>{{cite news|url=http://www.rumba.fi/perjantaina-omalaatuiset-levynjulkkarit-keskella-katua-julma-henri-ja-rpk-tarjoavat-euro-crackia-36454/|author= |title=Perjantaina omalaatuiset levynjulkkarit keskell\u00e4 katua \u2013 Julma-Henri ja RPK tarjoavat Euro Crackia|publisher=Rumba.fi|date=28 June 2013|language=Finnish}}</ref>  (stylized as E U R O C R A C K) in 2012.\n\nJulma-Henri is known for his lurid and gritty sociopolitical lyrics. With names such as [[Steen1]] and Panama Rayo, he became famous for having remarkably darker, harder and more serious punk influenced lyrical tone compared to other Finnish rappers, who were famous for their relatively light-minded, punchline-centric lyrics. In the early 2000's, his music and public image were widely associated with [[anarchism]] and proletarian activism and he made a name for himself by performing in illegal parties, political protests and even riots. \n\n==Career==\nJulma-Henri began his career at Forever, a rap band he formed in Oulu in 1998 under the pseudonym Money. The band released the single \"Mobmusic\", a demo EP in 2000. The other members were OeO, Reksa ja Leijona. As Money, he released ''Soundtrack 2 My Life'', a self-financed and independently released album produced by RK-62 and Panama Rayo. In 2003, cooperated with Asa and [[Steen1]]. A number of collaborations followed and he appeared in mixtapes and compilations with notable tracks like \"Mit\u00e4 s\u00e4 tied\u00e4t\" and \"Vaan sil on v\u00e4li\u00e4\". In 2004, he worked on ''Soundtrack 2 My Life'' as a full album with appearances by Steen1, Tasis, Travis Bicle and Afu Ra (USA) \u2013 however, the album was never released.\n\nJulma-Henri found recognition with his debut studio album ''Al-Qaida Finland'' in 2005 while still residing in Oulu. In many of his releases, he used the name '''Julma-Henri & Syrj\u00e4ytyneet''' (Julma-Henri and the Marginalized). Julma-Henri always appears disguised without revealing much of his face. In 2005 and 2006, he had a joint radio show Bassoradio (a collective project of tens of DJs) with Steen 1 as ''Julma-Henri & Yst\u00e4v\u00e4t'' (meaning Julma-Henri & Friends) The title was \"Free Your Mind\" also touring Finland with Asa and Steen 1 and appearing in tracks in releases by them. In 2007, he appeared in a music video with Asa called \"240306\" (aka \"RikRek\"). In May 2007, Panama Rayon and Laineen Kasper reproduced and rereleased Julma-Henri's ''Al-Qaida Finland'' on Colin Records in Helsinki with great success. In January 2008, an all-Finland \"Support Al-Qaida Finland Tour\" was organized assisted by a number of rap and hip hop acts.\n\nBased on this success, he released in December 2008 the mixtape ''SRJTNT Vol 1'' criticizing commercialization of rap. It was produced by Panama Rayo. A number of appearances followed in a series of compilations like Asa's ''Via Karelia'', Aisti & Emeto's ''Exitus'' in the title track and Leijona's album ''Vauhtia ja vaarallisia tilanteita''. His 2009 release ''Outo nauha'' was a split album with Laineen Kasperi. In 2010, he released the album ''Psykoterapia'' again crediting Julma-Henri & Syrj\u00e4ytyneet and dealing, as many of his earlier albums with social exclusion and mental health problems and the dark side of life. The album was released on M\u00f6rssi record label and distributed by Playground Music. A single titled \"Kipu\" (meaning Pain) was released as a single. After ''Psykoterapia'', Julma-Henri & Syrj\u00e4ytyneet assembly broke in 2010 due to disagreements and Julma-Henri proceeded on collaborations with rapper [[RPK (rapper)|RPK]] (of Ceebrolistics fame) with joint ''Kutsu EP'' of 6 tracks released in December 2010 credited to '''Julma-Henri & RPK'''. \"Kutsu\" taken from the album was released as a music video. The follow-up album ''\"HENRI\"'' with 17 tracks from Julma-Henri & RPK in February 2013 produced another music video \"Pala\". Julma-Henri also contributed tracks to albums by Juju and Jontti.\n\nIn December 2011, Julma-Henri released his new album ''Radio Jihad... SRJTNT vol. 2''<ref name=nrgm>[http://www.nrgm.fi/kritiikit/julma-henri-radio-jihad-syrjaytynyt-vol-2/ nrgm.fi Review of Julma-Henri album \u2013 ''Radio Jihad: Syrj\u00e4ytynyt vol. 2''] {{in lang|fi}}</ref> as a follow-up to his successful ''SRJTNT Vol 1''  touching subjects of personal growth, recovery and hope from society's ills. The album was produced by DJ Polarsoul and a number of artists contributed including Asa, Jontti, Juju, Konna, RPK, Super Janne, C-star, Akli ja Joska. Three music videos were released: \"Punainen\", \"Radio Jihad\" and \"Kauppaan kauppaan\"\n\n===Eurocrack===\n{{Main|Eurocrack}}\nAs early as July 2011, and prior to ''Radio Jihad...'' release by Julma-Henri, RPK announced on [[Bassoradio]] that he was collaborating with Julma-Henri on a brand new project called Eurocrack and that an album was in the offing. In preparation, the two released ''Euro Crack EP'' in the July 2012.<ref>{{cite web|last=Tamminen|first=Jari|title=Julma Henri, hyvien puolella|url=http://fifi.voima.fi/artikkeli/2012/heinakuu/julma-henri-hyvien-puolella|publisher=Fifi.voima.fi|accessdate=29 April 2014}}</ref> The EP contained 7 tracks including the epominous ''E.U.R.O.C.R.A.C.K.'' and the track \"Euro Crack Rocks\", the latter with Kube, Aztra, Khid, Klommo, Ameeba & Mindman. A promotional website www.eurocrack.com was launched in preparation. \"Pommi\" from the EP was released as a music video. The two organized a \"Euro Crack Tour\" to promote the project through M\u00f6rss website. The act also announced signing to the [[Fullsteam Records]] in cooperation with M\u00f6rssi.\n\nIn 2013, the track \"Douppii douppaa\" was released as pre-release in music video form in promotion of the debut studio album of Eurocrack (stylized as E U R O C R A C K). The album titled ''Huume'' (stylized as H U U M E) was released on 28 June 2013 entering the Finnish Albums Chart at number 7 in its first week of release.\n\n==Discography==\n\n===Albums, EPs, Mixtapes===\n'''as part of Forever'''\n*2000: ''Mobmusic'' (demo release)\n\n'''as Money'''\n*2003: ''Soundtrack 2 My Life'' <small>(self-released)</small>\n*2004: ''Mob. Ent: Live Mixtape'' <small>(self-released)</small>\n*2004: TBA <small>(full mixtape album, not released)</small>\n\n'''Julma-Henri & Syrj\u00e4ytyneet'''\n*2007: ''Al-Qaida Finland'' <small>(\u00c4hky Records)</small>\n*2008: ''SRJTNT vol. 1'' <small>(mixtape, self-released)</small>\n*2010: ''Psykoterapia'' <small>(M\u00f6rssi)</small>\n\n'''Henri & Kasperi'''\n*2009: ''Outo nauha'' <small>(aplit album with Laineen Kasperi. \u00c4hky Records)</small>\n\n'''Solo'''\n*2011: ''Radio Jihad... SRJTNT vol. 2'' <small>(M\u00f6rssi)</small>\n\n'''as Julma-Henri & RPK'''\n*2010: ''Kutsu EP'' <small>(M\u00f6rssi)</small>\n*2011: ''\"HENRI\"'' <small>(M\u00f6rssi)</small>\n\n'''as Julma-Henri vs RPK'''\n*2012: ''Euro Crack EP'' <small>(M\u00f6rssi)</small>\n\n'''as [[Eurocrack]]'''\n*2013: ''H U U M E'' <small>(M\u00f6rssi / [[Fullsteam Records]])</small>\n\n'''as JULMA H'''\n*2015: JULMA H (M\u00f6rssi / Fullsteam Records)\n*2016: Julma H: Kuka muu muka 2 (M\u00f6rssi Records)\n*2016: Julma H: Musta Albumi (Playground / M\u00f6rssi Records)\n\n===Singles / Music videos===\n*2007: \"240306\" aka \"RikRek\" <small>(Julma-Henri & Syrj\u00e4ytyneet featuring Asa)</small>\n*2009: \"Meitsi on matafaka\" <small>(Julma-Henri & Syrj\u00e4ytyneet)</small>\n*2010: \"Kipu\" <small>(Julma-Henri & Syrj\u00e4ytyneet)</small>\n*2010: \"Kutsu\" <small>(Julma-Henri & RPK)</small>\n*2011: \"Pala\"  <small>(Julma-Henri & RPK)</small>\n*2011: \"Punainen\" <small>(Julma-Henri featuring RPK)</small>\n*2011: \"Radio Jihad\" <small>(Julma-Henri)</small>\n*2012: \"Kauppaan kauppaan\" <small>(Julma-Henri)</small>\n*2012: \"E.U.R.O.C.R.A.C.K.\"  <small>(JLMA HNRI x RPK)</small>\n*2012: \"Savuaa\" <small>(Juju featuring Julma-Henri)</small>\n\n'''Euro Crack / Eurocrack single / music video releases'''\n*2012: \"Pommi\" <small>(JLMA HNRI X RPK / EURO CRACK)</small>\n*2013: \"Spaced Out\" <small>(Eurocrack)</small>\n*2013: \"Douppii douppaa\" <small>(Eurocrack)</small>\n*2013: \"Kr\u00e4kk\u00e4kr\u00e4nkk\u00e4\" <small>(Eurocrack)</small>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://www.facebook.com/JulmaHenri Facebook]\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Julma-Henri}}\n[[Category:Finnish rappers]]\n[[Category:Masked musicians]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Oulu]]\n[[Category:Horrorcore artists]]\n[[Category:Grime music artists]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n", "name_user": "Majavah", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200etop:clean up,typo(s) fixed: 2000's \u2192 2000s", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Julma-Henri"}
